  "category": "dkc",
  "description": "DKC (Dunning-Kruger Coding) detection rules. 56 rules across 7 weighted categories for identifying code shipped without adequate understanding. Each rule maps to a category phase and carries severity, detection method, and applicable cross-references to the VantaCode MBT taxonomy.",
  "name": "VantaCode DKC Rules",
  "source": "https://github.com/vantacode/vantacode-taxonomies",
  "type": "vantacode-dkc-rules",
  "uuid": "d3f6a89c-5e44-4cf3-be21-3d4c6f7e9fa3",
  "version": 1,
  "values": [
    {
      "description": "Comments that read like LLM responses rather than developer notes. 'Here is the code that handles authentication as you requested' is not a comment a developer writes. Detection method: regex. Fix: Review each flagged comment. If the code it describes is functional and understood, rewrite the comment to be useful. If the code is NOT understood, that's the real problem - the comment is just the symptom.",
      "meta": {
        "kill_chain": [
          "vantacode-dkc:comment-forensics"
        ],
        "refs": [
          "https://github.com/vantacode",
          "https://github.com/vantacode/vantacode-taxonomies"
        ],
        "severity": "medium",
        "category": "Comment Forensics",
        "category-weight": 0.1,
        "rule-id": "CMT-001",
        "related-taxonomies": [
          "vantacode-mbt:adversarial-input-vulnerabilities=\"prompt-injection\""
        ],
        "detection-method": "regex"
      },
      "uuid": "e149b57b-0363-533d-b622-7a6e048eb7b8",
      "value": "LLM Chat Response Left as Comments - CMT-001"
    },
    {
      "description": "Comments that explicitly or implicitly indicate the developer doesn't understand what the code does. This is the clearest DKC signal possible - the developer telling you they don't know what they shipped. Detection method: regex. Fix: Every comment flagged here represents code that needs to be understood before it should be in production. If you can't explain what a block does without AI help, it shouldn't be handling your users' data.",
      "meta": {
        "kill_chain": [
          "vantacode-dkc:comment-forensics"
        ],
        "refs": [
          "https://github.com/vantacode",
          "https://github.com/vantacode/vantacode-taxonomies"
        ],
        "severity": "high",
        "category": "Comment Forensics",
        "category-weight": 0.1,
        "rule-id": "CMT-002",
        "related-taxonomies": [
          "vantacode-mbt:adversarial-input-vulnerabilities=\"prompt-injection\""
        ],
        "detection-method": "regex"
      },
      "uuid": "c8013980-fa3d-5f7d-ad03-43a6d2b225b3",
      "value": "Comments Indicating Developer Doesn't Understand the Code - CMT-002"
    },
    {
      "description": "TODO/FIXME comments specifically about security features that were never implemented. The LLM generated a placeholder comment promising security 'later' and the developer shipped it as-is. Detection method: regex_plus_verification. Fix: Each security TODO needs to be either implemented or explicitly acknowledged as accepted risk with justification. 'TODO: add rate limiting' on a login endpoint is not an acceptable state for a deployed application.",
      "meta": {
        "kill_chain": [
          "vantacode-dkc:comment-forensics"
        ],
        "refs": [
          "https://github.com/vantacode",
          "https://github.com/vantacode/vantacode-taxonomies"
        ],
        "severity": "critical",
        "category": "Comment Forensics",
        "category-weight": 0.1,
        "rule-id": "CMT-003",
        "related-taxonomies": [
          "vantacode-mbt:adversarial-input-vulnerabilities=\"prompt-injection\""
        ],
        "detection-method": "regex_plus_verification"
      },
      "uuid": "8874c00a-eef1-51f8-b916-c9aad7fdd782",
      "value": "Security Features Deferred to TODO and Never Implemented - CMT-003"
    },
    {
      "description": "Security mechanisms (auth checks, validation, CSRF protection, rate limiting) that exist in the code but are commented out. Worse than never having them - someone (or some LLM session) added security and then a later session disabled it. Detection method: regex. Fix: Uncomment and properly configure the security mechanism. If it was commented out because it caused errors, fix the errors - don't remove the security.",
      "meta": {
        "kill_chain": [
          "vantacode-dkc:comment-forensics"
        ],
        "refs": [
          "https://github.com/vantacode",
          "https://github.com/vantacode/vantacode-taxonomies"
        ],
        "severity": "critical",
        "category": "Comment Forensics",
        "category-weight": 0.1,
        "rule-id": "CMT-004",
        "related-taxonomies": [
          "vantacode-mbt:adversarial-input-vulnerabilities=\"prompt-injection\""
        ],
        "detection-method": "regex"
      },
      "uuid": "bcd5f277-775f-5040-93a3-f96172394e0f",
      "value": "Security Code Commented Out - CMT-004"
    },
    {
      "description": "Inverse signal: complex code blocks (regex, crypto operations, auth flows, database transactions, bitwise operations) with no comments at all, while trivial code nearby has verbose LLM-style comments. The LLM documented the obvious and left the hard parts unexplained - because the developer never asked about the hard parts. Detection method: ast_and_heuristic. Fix: Add meaningful comments explaining the WHY of complex logic. If you can't explain it, you shouldn't be shipping it.",
      "meta": {
        "kill_chain": [
          "vantacode-dkc:comment-forensics"
        ],
        "refs": [
          "https://github.com/vantacode",
          "https://github.com/vantacode/vantacode-taxonomies"
        ],
        "severity": "high",
        "category": "Comment Forensics",
        "category-weight": 0.1,
        "rule-id": "CMT-005",
        "related-taxonomies": [
          "vantacode-mbt:adversarial-input-vulnerabilities=\"prompt-injection\""
        ],
        "detection-method": "ast_and_heuristic"
      },
      "uuid": "20f895b2-8adb-549b-b846-c1aec18ad7c6",
      "value": "Complex Logic With Zero Comments - CMT-005"
    },
    {
      "description": "Comments tracking which version of the AI generated which part of the code. Confirms multi-session LLM development without architectural coherence. Detection method: regex.",
      "meta": {
        "kill_chain": [
          "vantacode-dkc:comment-forensics"
        ],
        "refs": [
          "https://github.com/vantacode",
          "https://github.com/vantacode/vantacode-taxonomies"
        ],
        "severity": "medium",
        "category": "Comment Forensics",
        "category-weight": 0.1,
        "rule-id": "CMT-006",
        "related-taxonomies": [
          "vantacode-mbt:adversarial-input-vulnerabilities=\"prompt-injection\""
        ],
        "detection-method": "regex"
      },
      "uuid": "8e5f05b5-867d-59a9-890c-1d26a71b27d6",
      "value": "LLM Session History in Comments - CMT-006"
    },
    {
      "description": "Credentials, API keys, or passwords left in comments - often from LLM examples that used placeholder values the developer then replaced with real ones in code but left the original in a comment. Detection method: regex.",
      "meta": {
        "kill_chain": [
          "vantacode-dkc:comment-forensics"
        ],
        "refs": [
          "https://github.com/vantacode",
          "https://github.com/vantacode/vantacode-taxonomies"
        ],
        "severity": "critical",
        "category": "Comment Forensics",
        "category-weight": 0.1,
        "rule-id": "CMT-007",
        "related-taxonomies": [
          "vantacode-mbt:adversarial-input-vulnerabilities=\"prompt-injection\""
        ],
        "detection-method": "regex"
      },
      "uuid": "98bb9f1e-c8ac-568a-8a30-7445e8d77e68",
      "value": "Comments Containing Credentials or Secrets - CMT-007"
    },
    {
      "description": "Comments saying something is temporary, for testing, or will be removed - but the code has been deployed. 'Temporary' auth bypass in production is a backdoor. Detection method: regex. Fix: Either implement the proper solution or remove the feature. 'Temporary' code in production is permanent code with no accountability.",
      "meta": {
        "kill_chain": [
          "vantacode-dkc:comment-forensics"
        ],
        "refs": [
          "https://github.com/vantacode",
          "https://github.com/vantacode/vantacode-taxonomies"
        ],
        "severity": "critical",
        "category": "Comment Forensics",
        "category-weight": 0.1,
        "rule-id": "CMT-008",
        "related-taxonomies": [
          "vantacode-mbt:adversarial-input-vulnerabilities=\"prompt-injection\""
        ],
        "detection-method": "regex"
      },
      "uuid": "0c395915-cd1c-5ccc-a0a7-aefdc4df4511",
      "value": "Temporary Bypasses That Became Permanent - CMT-008"
    },
    {
      "description": "Code references functions, classes, config files, environment variables, or API endpoints that don't exist anywhere in the repo. Detection method: static_analysis. Fix: Each phantom reference is either dead code (remove it) or a missing implementation (implement it). There is no third option.",
      "meta": {
        "kill_chain": [
          "vantacode-dkc:llm-fingerprints"
        ],
        "refs": [
          "https://github.com/vantacode",
          "https://github.com/vantacode/vantacode-taxonomies"
        ],
        "severity": "high",
        "category": "LLM Code Fingerprints",
        "category-weight": 0.1,
        "rule-id": "LLM-001",
        "related-taxonomies": [
          "vantacode-mbt:adversarial-input-vulnerabilities=\"prompt-injection\"",
          "vantacode-mbt:ai-supply-chain-threats=\"malicious-ml-dependency\""
        ],
        "detection-method": "static_analysis"
      },
      "uuid": "81b166ec-e292-53d9-a707-d374442e0336",
      "value": "References to Non-Existent Code - LLM-001"
    },
    {
      "description": "Package imports referencing npm/PyPI/crates packages that have never existed. Also a supply chain attack vector. Detection method: registry_verification. Fix: Identify what the hallucinated package was supposed to do. Find a real, maintained package that does it. Or write the functionality yourself.",
      "meta": {
        "kill_chain": [
          "vantacode-dkc:llm-fingerprints"
        ],
        "refs": [
          "https://github.com/vantacode",
          "https://github.com/vantacode/vantacode-taxonomies"
