    {
      "description": "API keys, passwords, tokens, private keys in source or config committed to repo. Scans ALL git history. Detection method: secret_scanning. Tools: trufflehog, gitleaks, detect-secrets. Fix: 1. Rotate ALL exposed credentials immediately (they're already compromised if the repo was ever public). 2. Move secrets to environment variables. 3. Add .env to .gitignore. 4. Use git-filter-repo to purge from history. 5. Consider using a secrets manager.",
      "meta": {
        "kill_chain": [
          "vantacode-dkc:security-anti-patterns"
        ],
        "refs": [
          "https://github.com/vantacode",
          "https://github.com/vantacode/vantacode-taxonomies"
